<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1444] Using -Djvmflags option causes NoClassDefFoundError</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1444</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When starting tests with the -Djvmflags option, the harness (RunList class) places &quot;&quot; around the argument to -Djvmflags when executing the java launcher to start a new jvm. This is (at least by suns java launcher) interpreted as a Class and not as a command line option, because of the &quot;&quot;. Because of this I get a NoClassDefFoundError.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe this is a problem that happens only when using Suns java launcher.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Suns jvm 1.5</environment>
